The '''Power 5 heavy blaster pistol''' was a [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] manufactured by [[Merr-Sonn Munitions, Inc./Legends|Merr-Sonn Munitions, Inc.]] at some point prior to the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].

It was designed to imitate the more successful [[BlasTech Industries/Legends|BlasTech Industries]] [[DL-44 heavy blaster pistol/Legends|DL-44]] [[Heavy blaster pistol/Legends|heavy blaster pistol]].<ref name="Arms" /> Like the DL-44, the Power 5 was a high-powered, short-ranged weapon. The Power 5's [[Blaster gas/Legends|blaster gas]] chamber was smaller than that of the DL-44, and not very efficient. As a result the pistol was less powerful, but could fire more bolts per [[Power cell/Legends|power cell]].{{Fact}} There is both a long-barreled<ref name="Arms" /> and short-barreled variant of the weapon.<ref name="Champions">{{SWGTCG|set=Champions of the Force|cardname=Power 5 Pistol}}</ref>

The Power 5 was a favorite of [[Nym/Legends|Nym's]] private pirate army.<ref name="Champions" /> [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] was known to have used this weapon on occasion during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].<ref name="RoC1">[[River of Chaos 1|''River of Chaos'' 1]]</ref>

{{Weapon-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:Power_5_egwt.png|thumb|left|180px|Power 5 [[:Category:Technical drawing images|schematics]].]]
Like the DL-44, the Power 5 is a [[Wikipedia:Mauser C96|"Broomhandle" Mauser C96]] with cosmetic attachments. There has been some confusion in sources over the years between the Power 5 and the [[Model 44 blaster pistol]], which are very similar in appearance except that one has a cut-off barrel. Whereas many sources state that the full-barrelled blaster is the Power 5 and the cut-off version as the Model 44, [[Star Wars Galaxies]] and its [[Star Wars Galaxies Trading Card Game|Trading Card Game]] list the cut-off barrelled version as the Power 5.

The original image of the Model 44 from the ''[[Star Wars Customizable Card Game]]'' appears to be based on a photo of the same prop that was the basis for the Power 5 pistol, but incomplete or broken.<ref name="CCG Premiere">{{CCG|set=Premiere Limited|cardname=Blaster}}</ref> ''[[Star Wars: Behind the Magic]]'' includes a behind the scenes photo of the incomplete prop captioned "A heavy blaster under construction." ''Behind the Magic'' also erroneously identifies [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker's]] [[Model 57/Legends|Model 57]] as a Power 5.<ref name="BtM">''[[Star Wars: Behind the Magic]]''</ref>

In ''[[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|A New Hope]]'' the full-barreled Power 5 is seen holstered with the [[Death Star]] [[Gantry officer/Legends|gantry officers]], as well as in promotional images wielded by [[Leia Skywalker Organa Solo|Princess Leia]].

In the Hasbro Star Wars [[Star Wars: 30th Anniversary Collection|30th Anniversary Collection]] "Jawa and LIN Droid" action figure set, the Jawa carries a Power 5 pistol with a full barrel and downsized grip for his smaller hands. On the cover of [[The Paradise Snare]], [[Bria Tharen]] can be seen wielding a Power-5 with the full barrel.<ref name="Hasbro">{{HasbroCite|set=Star Wars: 30th Anniversary Collection|pack=#19: Jawa & LIN Droid (Tatooine Scavenger)|altlink=https://www.rebelscum.com/TAC19jawa.asp}}</ref>

